  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal profile)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. The assessment evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Intended use is restricted to adult CPB circuits operating at flow rates 2–7 L/min and pump speeds 1500–3500 RPM; outputs are the normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) and shear-stress exposure histograms. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Decision: Accepted.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/morrison/req/cpb-hemolysis-mrl2",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/morrison/claim/cpb-hemolysis-worst-case",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/morrison/model/cfd-hemolysis-v3",
  "bindsDataset": [
    "https://uofa.net/morrison/data/fda-pump-piv-experimental",
    "https://uofa.net/morrison/data/fda-pump-hemolysis-bench"
  ],
